  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "General Operation Manager (Restaurant)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>1. Outlet Visits & Operational Supervision</strong></h2><ul><li>Visit multiple outlets daily to monitor overall performance.</li><li>Ensure strict execution of SOPs (Front-of-House, Back-of-House, food handling, cashiering, safety procedures).</li><li>Maintain high standards of service quality, food quality, hygiene, and cleanliness.</li><li>Identify operational issues on-site, provide immediate feedback, and follow up on improvements.</li></ul><h2><strong>2. Staff Performance & Team Support</strong></h2><ul><li>Observe performance of managers, supervisors, and frontline staff; identify training needs.</li><li>Guide and support outlet teams to improve service standards and operational efficiency.</li><li>Monitor overall staff morale and assist in resolving operational challenges.</li></ul><h2><strong>3. Process Management & Improvement</strong></h2><ul><li>Review inventory processes to ensure accurate stock usage and minimal wastage.</li><li>Implement improvements to increase efficiency and standardization across outlets.</li><li>Support process optimization to ensure consistent product quality.</li></ul><h2><strong>4. Reporting & Operational Analysis</strong></h2><ul><li>Prepare regular outlet inspection reports with key findings and improvement actions.</li><li>Analyse operational KPIs, including sales, costs, manpower, and wastage.</li><li>Provide recommendations to enhance overall operational performance.</li></ul><h2><strong>5. Cross-Department Coordination</strong></h2><ul><li>Work closely with store managers, central kitchen, HR, procurement, and admin teams.</li><li>Support the implementation of new policies, menu items, and procedures.</li></ul><h1><strong>Requirements</strong></h1><ul><li>Minimum <strong>3 years of F&B management experience</strong> in Singapore.</li><li>Experience in multi-outlet supervision or area management is a strong advantage.</li><li>Able to travel across multiple outlets daily (East / West / North depending on assignment).</li><li>Strong understanding of F&B operations, SOP enforcement, food safety, and hygiene standards.</li><li>Strong problem-solving ability with confidence in making on-site decisions.</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills; able to work with diverse teams.</li><li><strong>English proficiency is required for effective workplace communication and reporting.</strong><br /><strong>Ability to communicate in Mandarin is an advantage to effectively liaise with Mandarin-speaking staff and suppliers</strong></li><li>Proactive, responsible, and able to work in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul><h1><br /></h1>",
